gnu.trove.decorator
Class TObjectLongMapDecorator<K>

java.lang.Object
  java.util.AbstractMap<K,java.lang.Long>
      gnu.trove.decorator.TObjectLongMapDecorator<K>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<K,java.lang.Long>
public class TObjectLongMapDecorator<K>
extends java.util.AbstractMap<K,java.lang.Long>
implements java.util.Map<K,java.lang.Long>, java.io.Externalizable, java.lang.Cloneable

Wrapper class to make a TObjectLongMap conform to the java.util.Map API. This class simply decorates an underlying TObjectLongMap and translates the Object-based APIs into their Trove primitive analogs.

Note that wrapping and unwrapping primitive values is extremely inefficient. If possible, users of this class should override the appropriate methods in this class and use a table of canonical values.

Created: Mon Sep 23 22:07:40 PDT 2002
